<LP>
   LONDON -- BBA Group PLC, a British auto and aviation parts
manufacturer, said it agreed to buy a Dallas-based aerospace
parts subsidiary of Hillman Co. in exchange for a 4.99% stake
in BBA.
   BBA is to acquire Texstar Inc., which makes high
technology plastic parts and composite materials for the
aerospace industry.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Hillman will receive 11,960,000 BBA ordinary shares, which
at 138.5 pence a share price values the deal at #16.6
million.
   Textar had an operating profit of $4.3 million last year
on sales of $32 million, with commercial and military
aerospace markets accounting for 60% of the sales.
</TEXT>
